column4: Why is it that my edgy eft desktop doesn't keep the time syncd despite it being checked to "keep clock synchronized with internet servers"?
i have to disable that check box and press synchonize now to make the time correct?
Anybody here?

I was writing a wiki and now I have a msg at the top saying it should be moved to https://help.ubuntu.com/community where other people would not be able to modify it. I disagree. Am I going to be forced to do that?

I was writing a wiki at the ubuntu site https://wiki.ubuntu.com/ and now I have a msg at the top saying it should be moved to https://help.ubuntu.com/community where other people would not be able to modify it. I disagree. Am I going to be forced to do that?
i think community given documentation should go in /community, it allows others to edit it so i dont think it should be telling you the opposite :-)
i'm confused, the wiki is where everybody can update it and is where it is currently. /community is where they are telling me to put it and that seems to be static.
are you logged in? https://help.ubuntu.com/community/ -> this isn't static
hmmm, ok, i'll check it out.
i hope you can sort it. thanks for contributing :-)
why would they want to take it away from the obvious place, the wiki, where everybody instinctively knows they can change it?
i go to community and it looks like a mess and it's not even obvious i can sign in
i'm not sure. i can edit pages on wiki.ubuntu.com. i've got a suspicion it has something todo with signing the ubuntu code of conduct but i could be wrong?
again i'm confused. wiki.ubuntu.com is fine and is where i am writing the documentation and is the natural place in my mind to add user supplied documentation.
they however say: This document should be moved to the documentation wiki at https://help.ubuntu.com/community
i'm confuzzled to. what page are you editing?
reading the paste just now i see my error, there is some wiki somewhere else besides https://wiki.ubuntu.com/...
i'll poke around at https://help.ubuntu.com/community until i find a wiki there...
help.ubuntu.com/community is a wiki o_O
oh, silly me, didn't see wiki in it's url so assumed it was static.
ah :-)
